        "content": "<p>Addressing <a href=\"https://github.com/zulip/zulip/pull/5804\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/zulip/zulip/pull/5804\">#5804</a>, Update logged-out/portico pages to be aware of user login status:</p>\n<p>Currently, the header on portico pages always displays 'Login' and 'Register' links. If a user is logged in, it would be nice to replace the upper-right 'Log in' and 'Register' links with, respectively, 'Log out' and 'Go to Zulip' / an avatar icon. It might also be good to visually highlight the 'Register' link as a CTA.</p>\n<p>Thoughts?</p>",
